<subSubSection lastPageId="86" lastPageNumber="87" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,1260,2042]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1872,1898]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is a rare species previously known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[907,993,1872,1898]" name="Finland" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Finland</collectingCountry>
and Yakutia, 
<collectingCountry box="[1152,1227,1872,1898]" name="Russia" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Vasilenko, S. V." pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="31 - 37" refId="ref78999" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Vasilenko, S. V. (2005) Some pamphiliid sawflies (Hymenoptera) in the collection of the Siberian Zoological Museum, Novosibirsk. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 11, 31 - 37." type="journal article" year="2005">Shinohara &amp; Vasilenko 2005</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record from 
<collectingCountry box="[660,732,1909,1935]" name="South Korea" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Korea</collectingCountry>
. The larvae are gregarious web-spinners on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vikberg 2002)" baseAuthorityName="Vikberg" baseAuthorityYear="2002" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1249,1327,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Sorbus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vikberg, V." pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="439 - 459" refId="ref80692" refString="Vikberg, V. (2002) Rearing experiments on Finnish species of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera), with special emphasis on the egg laying behaviour. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 439 - 459." type="book chapter" year="2002">Vikberg 2002</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Another species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1803" box="[451,579,1944,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,579,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Pamphilius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose larvae are gregarious web-spinners on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vikberg" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[1113,1191,1944,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1113,1191,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Sorbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1985" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="montanus" subSpecies="montanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">P. montanus montanus</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1985
</taxonomicName>
, from Honshu, 
<collectingCountry box="[581,645,1981,2007]" name="Japan" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H." box="[659,962,1980,2006]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="27 - 33" refId="ref78349" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H. (2011) Host plants and larvae of two sawfly species of the Pamphilius sylvaticus group (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) in Japan. Bulletin of the National Museum of Nature and Science, Tokyo, Series A, 37, 27 - 33." type="journal article" year="2011">Shinohara &amp; Kojima 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The larvae of these two species have not been differentiated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
The Korean specimens examined differ from the Finnish specimens in a darker colour pattern. In Korean females, the entire tergum 1, large areas on the terga 2 and 6 and the entire terga 7 and 8 are black and all the sterna are broadly black basally. In Finnish females, the entire tergum 1 and very narrow areas on the terga 2 and 6 to 8 are black and the sterna 2, 3, 6 and 7 are marked with black basally. In almost all males from 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1267,259,285]" name="South Korea" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Korea</collectingCountry>
, the postocular stripe terminates at the corner of the upper inner orbits, whereas the postocular stripe extends ventrally along the inner orbits in the Finnish males (see fig. 
<quantity box="[626,670,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Vikberg, V." box="[678,835,331,357]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="140 - 145" refId="ref80660" refString="Vikberg, V. (1971) Pamphilius aucupariae sp. n. (Hym., Pamphiliidae) from Finland. Annales Entomologici Fennici, 37, 140 - 145." type="journal article" year="1971">Vikberg 1971</bibRefCitation>
). In structural characters, no conspicuous differences have been found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
In our molecular analysis, the maximum intraspecific 
<emphasis box="[824,838,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">p</emphasis>
-distance was 1.3% in COI (n=4) and 0.1% in NaK (n=4). The nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fallen, 1808)" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1986" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[532,828,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteatus">
<emphasis box="[532,662,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. balteatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fallen, C. F." box="[676,821,439,465]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="219 - 227" refId="ref73308" refString="Fallen, C. F. (1808) Forsok till uppstallning och beskrifning a de i Sverige fundne Arter af Insect-Slagtet Tenthredo Linn. Kongl. Vetenskaps Academiens nya Handlingar, Stockholm, 29, 219 - 227." type="journal article" year="1808">Fallén, 1808</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 3.7% in the COI analysis, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 2005" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" box="[198,516,474,501]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[198,323,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. confusus</emphasis>
Shinohara, 2005
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 0.4%, in the NaK analysis. In the COI tree (
<figureCitation box="[1326,1423,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 151" captionStartId="238.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[163,1422,186,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-26@238.[157,1430,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="238" captionText="FIGURE 151. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876865" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876865/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 151</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="V. Vikberg" authorityYear="1971" box="[151,306,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aucupariae">
<emphasis box="[151,306,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. aucupariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
branched off near the base of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[683,768,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[683,768,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and its affinities are unclear, whereas in the NaK tree (
<figureCitation box="[159,255,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 161" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[177,1403,189,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@246.[171,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 161. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876886/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 161</figureCitation>
) it was retrieved as sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Taeger" authorityYear="2007" box="[575,658,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleji">
<emphasis box="[575,658,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. leleji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with UFBoot support of 98%.
</paragraph>
